title: Don't Trust Myself
lyrics:
And when you held me
I know in the moment I was falling from heaven
I wanna believe in something
Something so different
I'm stuck in the fever of us
Wish that love was overrated

And when I found you, I put my arms around you

Wanna feel special

Act the way that I'm supposed to

Feel on my own

I feel so alone

I don't want you to go



I can't get you out of my brain

You out of my brain

I don't trust myself

I'm under your spell

Oh baby, you must be full of yourself

Stuck on my brain



And when you held her

I knew in the moment I was falling into nothing

I wanna believe in you

But you are no different, baby

I'm stuck in the fever of us

Wish I was exaggerating

And I go to parties

I drink up all my money

How am I lonely?

So many other people 'round me?

Pick up the phone, I feel so alone

I need you to know



I can't get you out of my brain

You out of my brain

I don't trust myself

I'm under your spell

Oh baby, you must be full of yourself

Stuck on my brain
